data.text:
Part of our Retro collection, the LFC Adult Retro 95/96 Home Shirt is inspired by the jersey worn by the team during the 95/96 season.

During the 95/96 season Liverpool FC reached their second final in consecutive seasons, however this jersey will be remembered as the one worn for what many regard as the greatest Premier League game to date, when the Reds edged out Newcastle United 4-3 at Anfield with goals from club legends Robbie Fowler and an injury time winner from Stan Collymore. The jersey is a must-have for Reds with memories of this time or are building a collection.

The LFC 95-96 Home shirt features:

A 90s style crest on a red panel.

White and red stripe neck detail.

100% Cotton.

Machine washable.

Alternate Code: A11994
